1
00:00:25,634 --> 00:00:28,148
On his 35th birthday...

2
00:00:28,234 --> 00:00:31,306
I decided to tell
Julius Benedict...

3
00:00:31,394 --> 00:00:34,192
the truth about himself.

4
00:00:38,074 --> 00:00:40,668
Julius already knew
that he was the product...

5
00:00:40,754 --> 00:00:43,063
of a scientific
experiment...

6
00:00:43,154 --> 00:00:45,349
conducted by
the American government.

7
00:00:47,634 --> 00:00:51,309
A top-secret experiment designed
to produce a physically...

8
00:00:51,394 --> 00:00:55,069
mentally and spiritually
advanced human being.

9
00:00:58,834 --> 00:01:01,473
He knew that,
unlike other little boys...

10
00:01:01,554 --> 00:01:05,183
he had not one,
but six fathers--

11
00:01:05,274 --> 00:01:07,504
All very distinguished men...

12
00:01:07,594 --> 00:01:10,392
especially chosen for
their genetic excellence.

13
00:01:12,514 --> 00:01:14,345
And of course...

14
00:01:14,434 --> 00:01:17,471
he knew about
Mary Ann Benedict...

15
00:01:19,834 --> 00:01:22,029
the remarkable young woman...

16
00:01:22,114 --> 00:01:24,833
who was selected
to be his mother.

17
00:01:41,274 --> 00:01:44,823
Sadly, he had long lived
with the tragic knowledge...

18
00:01:44,914 --> 00:01:49,465
that his mother died
while giving birth to him.

19
00:01:53,234 --> 00:01:55,907
Now, what Julius
did not know...

20
00:01:55,994 --> 00:01:58,792
not until
this very moment...

21
00:01:58,874 --> 00:02:02,947
was that about a minute
after he was born...

22
00:02:03,034 --> 00:02:07,585
his mother gave birth
to another baby boy.

23
00:02:07,674 --> 00:02:09,790
[ Crying ]

24
00:02:15,634 --> 00:02:19,104
[ Crying ]

25
00:02:36,274 --> 00:02:38,947
[ Crying ]

26
00:02:53,594 --> 00:02:56,028
I have a brother ?

27
00:02:56,114 --> 00:02:58,230
Ya.

28
00:02:58,314 --> 00:03:00,782
He was sent to an
orphanage in Los Angeles...

29
00:03:00,874 --> 00:03:04,025
at the same time I brought
you here to the island.

30
00:03:05,874 --> 00:03:09,503
Julius had spent his entire life
here on the island...

31
00:03:09,594 --> 00:03:12,950
helping me with my research.

32
00:03:13,034 --> 00:03:16,265
I always thought he was happy,
and had no desire to leave.

33
00:03:16,354 --> 00:03:18,345
How wrong I was.

34
00:03:18,434 --> 00:03:21,392
I must find him.

35
00:03:23,914 --> 00:03:26,667
Julius, Julius ! Wait, wait.

36
00:03:28,594 --> 00:03:32,348
I couldn't believe he was going.

37
00:03:32,434 --> 00:03:36,109
He wasn't equipped to deal
with the outside world.

38
00:03:37,354 --> 00:03:40,505
All of his knowledge was from books.

39
00:03:41,674 --> 00:03:44,393
Julius could speak 12 languages.

40
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:46,829
He excelled in history, science...

41
00:03:46,914 --> 00:03:49,382
mathematics, literature.

42
00:03:49,474 --> 00:03:52,193
He was pure in body and in spirit.

43
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:53,309
Ahhh !

44
00:03:53,394 --> 00:03:56,227
But for the first time...

45
00:03:56,314 --> 00:03:58,430
Julius would not listen to me.

46
00:03:58,514 --> 00:04:01,870
He's probably just like me.

47
00:04:10,314 --> 00:04:14,990
The nearest island with
an airport was 27 miles away.

48
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,825
But Julius
did not care.

49
00:04:20,914 --> 00:04:23,382
He had become obsessed
with the idea...

50
00:04:23,474 --> 00:04:26,830
that his brother, Vincent,
was in some kind of trouble...

51
00:04:26,914 --> 00:04:30,065
and desperately
needed his help.

52
00:04:33,794 --> 00:04:35,864
Honey, I'm home !

53
00:04:35,954 --> 00:04:38,070
- Oh, no !
- Oh, no.

54
00:04:38,154 --> 00:04:40,509
- Get going !
- I'm going.

55
00:04:56,034 --> 00:04:59,470
[ Shaver Buzzing ]

56
00:05:03,874 --> 00:05:05,785
Oh, hello, hello !

57
00:05:05,874 --> 00:05:08,183
Oh, my goodness !

58
00:05:14,674 --> 00:05:17,108
Goodbye.

59
00:05:26,354 --> 00:05:29,187
- We're gonna be late for work.
- I need my horoscope.

60
00:05:29,274 --> 00:05:32,505
- Yeah, horoscope.
- ''Your judgment is at its peak today.

61
00:05:32,594 --> 00:05:35,586
Use it wisely,
and romance will follow.''

62
00:05:35,674 --> 00:05:39,110
- Ooh, good one.
- I hope so.

63
00:05:39,194 --> 00:05:41,310
Ladies !

64
00:05:41,394 --> 00:05:44,352
- Vince !
- I thought you broke up with him.

65
00:05:44,434 --> 00:05:46,311
I did, I did !

66
00:05:49,514 --> 00:05:53,666
- You don't mind if I talk
to your sister, do you ?
- She doesn't mind.

67
00:05:53,754 --> 00:05:55,870
Don't give him any money.

68
00:05:55,954 --> 00:06:00,505
Uh, no, no, I promised Marnie
I wouldn't give you any money.

69
00:06:00,594 --> 00:06:03,347
[ Whimpering ]

70
00:06:04,874 --> 00:06:07,468
Don't look at me like--

71
00:06:07,554 --> 00:06:10,227
Don't do that thing
with your eyes.

72
00:06:10,314 --> 00:06:13,750
I'm not even supposed
to be here with you.

73
00:06:13,834 --> 00:06:17,144
You are here,
and so am l.

74
00:06:17,234 --> 00:06:19,702
Maybe millions
of people go by...

75
00:06:19,794 --> 00:06:21,944
but they all
disappear from view.

76
00:06:22,034 --> 00:06:25,583
I only have eyes
for you, Linda.

77
00:06:25,674 --> 00:06:28,472
I only have
eyes for you.

78
00:06:30,114 --> 00:06:33,231
Mmm.

79
00:06:33,314 --> 00:06:37,148
- It's the baby klane !
- What ?

80
00:06:39,634 --> 00:06:41,545
- Hi.
- Hi.

81
00:06:41,634 --> 00:06:44,068
- Can I help you ?
- Uh, yeah.

82
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:46,543
Where's the little shit ?

83
00:06:46,634 --> 00:06:49,148
You'll have to be
more specific...

84
00:06:49,234 --> 00:06:51,384
concerning the clientele.

85
00:06:51,474 --> 00:06:53,385
Benedict.

86
00:06:53,474 --> 00:06:56,511
Oh, he wouldn't come in here.

87
00:06:56,594 --> 00:06:58,664
- Isn't that right, Marnie ?
- Who, Vincent ?

88
00:07:00,034 --> 00:07:03,743
That weasel ? That creep ?

89
00:07:03,834 --> 00:07:07,383
I wouldn't serve him if he crawled in
on his hands and knees.

90
00:07:27,074 --> 00:07:30,589
I knew you were trouble
the second I laid eyes on you.

91
00:07:30,674 --> 00:07:35,031
Excuse me. I just have never
heard this kind of music before.

92
00:08:23,354 --> 00:08:25,310
Thank you.

93
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:23,149
Hey, Vince !

94
00:09:23,234 --> 00:09:25,190
Listen, Al...

95
00:09:25,274 --> 00:09:27,310
you gotta help me out.

96
00:09:27,394 --> 00:09:29,828
I'm into the klane
brothers for $20,000.

97
00:09:29,914 --> 00:09:33,031
- You borrowed money from a loan shark ?
- What do you got ?

98
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:36,265
Got anything for me ?
See what you got.

99
00:09:36,354 --> 00:09:38,743
We're doing this
too often, Vince.

100
00:09:38,834 --> 00:09:40,825
I'll give you something.

101
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:43,951
I got a nice BMW
up on 4, stall 20.

102
00:10:09,034 --> 00:10:11,309
[ Engine Starts ]

103
00:10:11,394 --> 00:10:13,703
[ Tyres Screech ]

104
00:10:17,594 --> 00:10:20,506
Vince, I'll take all
of these you can get.

105
00:10:20,594 --> 00:10:23,267
[ Vince ]
All right, Tony.

106
00:10:23,354 --> 00:10:25,629
- For you.
- Thanks, Tony.

107
00:10:25,714 --> 00:10:27,545
Yeah.

108
00:10:27,634 --> 00:10:29,465
Whoa, Tony !

109
00:10:29,554 --> 00:10:33,866
There's only $4000 here.
For a car like this is $6000.

110
00:10:33,954 --> 00:10:36,514
We're in a recession.
Everything's tough.

111
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:39,233
You wanna try someone else,
no hard feelings.

112
00:10:39,314 --> 00:10:41,464
No, I just could've
used some more.

113
00:10:41,554 --> 00:10:44,022
- You okay, Vince ? You seem worried.
- Yeah.

114
00:10:44,114 --> 00:10:46,389
Your bowels troubling you ?

115
00:10:55,514 --> 00:10:58,028
What an amazing country.

116
00:10:58,994 --> 00:11:00,746
Hey.

117
00:11:00,834 --> 00:11:02,665
Gotta light, pal ?

118
00:11:02,754 --> 00:11:06,588
Oh, excuse me.
I don't smoke, pal.

119
00:11:06,674 --> 00:11:08,630
Yeah. Ha-ha.

120
00:11:08,714 --> 00:11:11,467
Yeah, good stuff, huh ?

121
00:11:11,554 --> 00:11:15,024
- Pickin' up something
for the girlfriend ?
- I don't have a girlfriend.

122
00:11:15,114 --> 00:11:17,423
Do women really
wear those things ?

123
00:11:17,514 --> 00:11:19,345
If you're lucky, they do.

124
00:11:19,434 --> 00:11:21,265
I can't believe it.

125
00:11:21,354 --> 00:11:23,345
- You're from out of town ?
- Yes.

126
00:11:23,434 --> 00:11:27,313
As a matter of fact, I come from
an island in the South Pacific.

127
00:11:27,394 --> 00:11:29,862
Whoa !

128
00:11:32,074 --> 00:11:34,634
What the hell did
you do to him, man !

129
00:11:34,714 --> 00:11:38,423
I did nothing.
The pavement was his enemy.

130
00:11:38,514 --> 00:11:42,268
Let me check him out.
A light concussion.

131
00:11:42,354 --> 00:11:44,026
Uh-oh.

132
00:11:44,114 --> 00:11:46,264
- I carry him to a hospital.
- No !

133
00:11:46,354 --> 00:11:48,584
I think you should
just take off, man.

134
00:11:48,674 --> 00:11:50,585
Find your horse
you came in on.

135
00:11:50,674 --> 00:11:52,471
I'm so sorry about this.

136
00:11:52,554 --> 00:11:55,432
- I feel terrible.
- Me, too. Thanks a lot.

137
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:57,470
- Sorry.
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

138
00:11:57,554 --> 00:12:01,024
The next time you should
really consider wearing helmets.

139
00:12:01,114 --> 00:12:03,070
Yeah, have a nice day.

140
00:12:03,154 --> 00:12:06,191
You don't have to buy them.
Just don't say they're cheap !

141
00:12:06,274 --> 00:12:09,744
These are quality socks.

142
00:12:09,834 --> 00:12:13,110
What a day it's been.
Oh, no, no, no !

143
00:12:13,194 --> 00:12:15,230
Oh, oh ! Jesus Christ !

144
00:12:15,314 --> 00:12:19,227
$53 ! Are you
out of your mind ?

145
00:12:19,314 --> 00:12:22,590
Your vehicle is in a handicapped zone,
if you didn't notice.

146
00:12:22,674 --> 00:12:24,869
So, do I look
normal to you ?

147
00:12:24,954 --> 00:12:27,070
You don't have a handicapped
sticker in your windshield.

148
00:12:27,154 --> 00:12:30,112
Oh, come on.
You don't need a sticker.

149
00:12:30,194 --> 00:12:32,105
Handicapped, my ass !

150
00:12:32,194 --> 00:12:34,867
I'll need your
driver's licence, sir.

151
00:12:34,954 --> 00:12:37,422
Look, I'm sorry
I lost my temper.

152
00:12:37,514 --> 00:12:39,345
Driver's licence,
please.

153
00:12:39,434 --> 00:12:42,187
- Look, I had a very bad day.
- Driver's licence... please.

154
00:12:42,274 --> 00:12:45,789
You've got over 200 outstanding
parking tickets, Mr Benedict.

155
00:12:45,874 --> 00:12:48,911
You just had your birthday.
Your driver's licence expired.

156
00:12:48,994 --> 00:12:50,905
Happy birthday.
Watch your head.

157
00:12:50,994 --> 00:12:52,950
Thanks.

158
00:12:54,954 --> 00:12:57,752
[ Bells Chiming ]

159
00:12:59,474 --> 00:13:01,385
Come along, now.

160
00:13:01,474 --> 00:13:03,863
[ Julius ] So this is where
my brother grew up.

161
00:13:03,954 --> 00:13:07,549
I'm so happy he had so many
children to play with.

162
00:13:11,714 --> 00:13:14,103
And that's where
he must have slept !

163
00:13:14,874 --> 00:13:16,705
Yes, it was.

164
00:13:16,794 --> 00:13:18,625
How did you know ?

165
00:13:18,714 --> 00:13:21,626
It's the one I'd have chosen,
close to the fire extinguisher.

166
00:13:21,714 --> 00:13:23,545
In case of a fire...

167
00:13:23,634 --> 00:13:26,910
I could have given the alarm
and saved all the other orphans.

168
00:13:28,154 --> 00:13:31,226
We've had only one fire
in here at St. Charlotte's.

169
00:13:31,314 --> 00:13:34,465
Vince Benedict started it,
we like to think by accident.

170
00:13:37,314 --> 00:13:40,272
Tell me a little bit
about Vincent.

171
00:13:40,354 --> 00:13:43,073
Was he a great athlete ?
lnterested in chess and poetry ?

172
00:13:43,154 --> 00:13:45,793
I'm certain God had a purpose
when he created Vince Benedict...

173
00:13:45,874 --> 00:13:48,547
but it had nothing
to do with chess or poetry.

174
00:13:48,634 --> 00:13:50,545
Oh, I'm sorry.

175
00:13:52,274 --> 00:13:55,346
Odd, the contents
of his files are missing.

176
00:13:56,914 --> 00:13:59,064
That is Vince ?

177
00:13:59,154 --> 00:14:01,065
He looks so happy.

178
00:14:01,154 --> 00:14:03,907
He should.
That's Sister Maria...

179
00:14:03,994 --> 00:14:06,462
- his biology teacher.
- I always liked biology.

180
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:08,351
So did Vincent.

181
00:14:08,434 --> 00:14:10,709
He disgraced Sister Maria...

182
00:14:10,794 --> 00:14:12,705
who had to leave the order.

183
00:14:12,794 --> 00:14:16,389
Then he stole all the money from
the library fund, and ran away.

184
00:14:16,474 --> 00:14:18,305
I must find my brother.

185
00:14:18,394 --> 00:14:20,703
Do you know
where he might be ?

186
00:14:20,794 --> 00:14:23,547
Jail, a man of his character
can only be in jail.

187
00:14:23,634 --> 00:14:27,627
You're full of goodness, Julius.
I pray you never find him.

188
00:14:31,474 --> 00:14:33,942
Benedict, visitor.

189
00:15:11,634 --> 00:15:14,102
[ Silence ]

190
00:15:21,394 --> 00:15:24,545
- I'm looking for Vincent Benedict.
- You got him.

191
00:15:48,354 --> 00:15:51,027
[ Silence ]

192
00:15:51,114 --> 00:15:53,469
I have rowed halfway
across the world--

193
00:15:53,554 --> 00:15:55,545
Wrong, I just rowed a day--

194
00:15:55,634 --> 00:15:58,706
[ Silence ]

195
00:15:58,794 --> 00:16:02,753
I've been looking forward to
this moment my whole life.

196
00:16:02,834 --> 00:16:05,223
I've been on my island,
I'm telling you.

197
00:16:05,314 --> 00:16:08,147
This is incredible that--
I have looked for--

198
00:16:08,234 --> 00:16:11,829
[ Silence ]

199
00:16:16,274 --> 00:16:19,152
You've gotta talk
into the phone, Bozo.

200
00:16:20,674 --> 00:16:23,427
Vincent.
Dearest, Vincent...

201
00:16:23,514 --> 00:16:25,789
I know you don't
know who I am.

202
00:16:25,874 --> 00:16:28,342
- But believe me, I came--
- Whoa, whoa, whoa !

203
00:16:28,434 --> 00:16:30,902
I've got another six hours
to pay the money back.

204
00:16:30,994 --> 00:16:34,031
Tell the klane brothers that harassing
a man already in the slammer...

205
00:16:34,114 --> 00:16:36,264
is beneath even them,
all right ?

206
00:16:36,354 --> 00:16:39,426
I don't know any klane brothers.
I'm your brother, Julius.

207
00:16:40,634 --> 00:16:43,432
Huh ? Come again ?

208
00:16:43,514 --> 00:16:46,904
My name is Julius,
and I'm your twin brother.

209
00:16:48,754 --> 00:16:50,585
Oh, obviously.

210
00:16:50,674 --> 00:16:55,384
The moment I sat down, I thought
I was looking into a mirror.

211
00:16:55,474 --> 00:16:57,829
We are not
identical twins.

212
00:16:57,914 --> 00:16:59,905
- Oh, no ?
- No.

213
00:16:59,994 --> 00:17:01,632
I wouldn't be
too sure, pal.

214
00:17:01,714 --> 00:17:03,545
I don't lie.
I am your brother.

215
00:17:03,634 --> 00:17:05,943
You must let me help
you get out of here.

216
00:17:06,034 --> 00:17:08,389
You want to
help me get out ?

217
00:17:08,474 --> 00:17:09,907
Yes, right now.

218
00:17:09,994 --> 00:17:13,703
Well, money talks,
and bullshit walks.

219
00:17:17,554 --> 00:17:20,273
How can bullshit walk ?
That's slang, huh ?

220
00:17:20,354 --> 00:17:21,946
Yeah.

221
00:17:22,034 --> 00:17:23,786
I'm in fast company here.

222
00:17:23,874 --> 00:17:26,342
Take a look over there.
See that man ?

223
00:17:26,434 --> 00:17:29,392
Pay him money, all right ?
They let me out.

224
00:17:29,474 --> 00:17:31,829
I'll be anything you want,
your aunt, uncle, sister...

225
00:17:31,914 --> 00:17:33,745
your cousin,
brother-in-law, anything.

226
00:17:33,834 --> 00:17:36,985
- All right ?
- Okay, I pay right now.

227
00:17:37,074 --> 00:17:38,587
- You pay now.
- Okay, Vince.

228
00:17:38,674 --> 00:17:40,665
Okay. Go pay.

229
00:17:40,754 --> 00:17:42,631
All right, pay him.

230
00:17:44,594 --> 00:17:47,062
What is this,
''Candid Camera'' ?

231
00:17:48,514 --> 00:17:50,709
Ahhh, oof !

232
00:17:52,394 --> 00:17:55,830
Twinny, I hope you didn't
blow your wad on the tickets...

233
00:17:55,914 --> 00:17:59,543
because I'm gonna need
a lot more money to get my car.

234
00:17:59,634 --> 00:18:01,545
- I have more money.
- You do ?

235
00:18:01,634 --> 00:18:04,592
I'm glad to help you.
Vincent, I'm your brother.

236
00:18:04,674 --> 00:18:06,824
- I love you.
- Whoa !

237
00:18:06,914 --> 00:18:09,792
Look, ease up
on the love talk...

238
00:18:09,874 --> 00:18:12,786
because I'm gonna be tossing
my cookies in a minute.

239
00:18:12,874 --> 00:18:14,944
Tossing your cookies ?

240
00:18:15,034 --> 00:18:16,831
Oh, that's more slang !

241
00:18:16,914 --> 00:18:19,223
[ Vincent ]
Where the hell is it ?

242
00:18:20,754 --> 00:18:24,667
- This is your car, isn't it ?
- Yeah, that's it.

243
00:18:24,754 --> 00:18:27,222
You pay a huge fine,
then they hide it on you.

244
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:30,306
- How'd you know this was my car ?
- We're twins !

245
00:18:30,394 --> 00:18:33,784
I'm so excited. Now we can
go to museums together...

246
00:18:33,874 --> 00:18:36,672
talk philosophy together,
read books together.

247
00:18:36,754 --> 00:18:39,109
- Play chess together.
- Get lost together.

248
00:18:42,914 --> 00:18:44,745
Vincent !

249
00:18:48,834 --> 00:18:51,223
He's so full of energy.

250
00:18:55,594 --> 00:18:57,346
Blue Sedan DeVille.

251
00:18:57,434 --> 00:18:59,868
This is beautiful.

252
