- Hit 'em, hit 'em.

1000
01:08:46,074 --> 01:08:48,349
Oh, hit 'em,
hit 'em.

1001
01:08:48,434 --> 01:08:50,345
Julius...

1002
01:08:50,434 --> 01:08:54,029
you know...

1003
01:08:54,114 --> 01:08:57,584
Julius, I have
to admit this.

1004
01:08:57,674 --> 01:09:00,746
Since you and I
first met, uh...

1005
01:09:00,834 --> 01:09:03,064
my life has been just
getting better and better.

1006
01:09:03,154 --> 01:09:06,385
Mine, too.

1007
01:09:06,474 --> 01:09:08,305
I'm so happy, Vincent.

1008
01:09:08,394 --> 01:09:10,669
I feel like
sometimes, like...

1009
01:09:10,754 --> 01:09:13,063
- picking you up and hug you...
- Whoa !

1010
01:09:13,154 --> 01:09:15,145
and hug you,
hug you, hug you.

1011
01:09:18,434 --> 01:09:20,265
Hey, he's my brother.

1012
01:09:20,354 --> 01:09:23,312
Oh, lay off
the beer, Julius.

1013
01:09:32,194 --> 01:09:35,630
Did you tell anyone
we were coming to Santa Fe ?

1014
01:09:35,714 --> 01:09:38,353
I called work and told them
we wouldn't be in for a few days.

1015
01:09:40,434 --> 01:09:42,504
Oh, I forgot to tell you
we were fired.

1016
01:09:42,594 --> 01:09:45,711
- Oh, no.
- You hated that job.

1017
01:09:45,794 --> 01:09:48,547
- Nice of your boss to tell us
where we could find you.
- Oh, no.

1018
01:09:48,634 --> 01:09:53,833
Hi, girls, you don't mind if
we join you and listen to some music.

1019
01:09:55,394 --> 01:10:00,229
The klane boys.
What an unpleasant surprise.

1020
01:10:00,314 --> 01:10:03,670
Vince, this has
gone way beyond...

1021
01:10:03,754 --> 01:10:06,951
- a case of simple loan delinquency.
- We don't like being shot.

1022
01:10:07,034 --> 01:10:10,026
Shot ? Who shot you ?

1023
01:10:10,114 --> 01:10:12,469
- What do you want ?
- We want to take Vince...

1024
01:10:12,554 --> 01:10:16,229
- out to the parking lot and kill him.
- Ohhh, owww !

1025
01:10:16,314 --> 01:10:19,465
Don't you think
that's a little drastic ?

1026
01:10:19,554 --> 01:10:21,192
Let's go.

1027
01:10:21,274 --> 01:10:23,185
Don't touch him.

1028
01:10:24,514 --> 01:10:26,152
Ohhh !

1029
01:10:26,234 --> 01:10:28,987
Hey, big fella.

1030
01:10:29,074 --> 01:10:31,349
You wouldn't want me to hurt
the lovely lady, would you ?

1031
01:10:31,434 --> 01:10:34,107
You moved too soon.

1032
01:10:35,434 --> 01:10:39,143
- What ?
- The second rule in a crisis:

1033
01:10:39,234 --> 01:10:41,873
Uh-oh. He's startin'
that funny talk, again.

1034
01:10:43,234 --> 01:10:45,225
If you choose to bluff...

1035
01:10:45,314 --> 01:10:47,270
you must be prepared
to have your bluff called.

1036
01:10:47,354 --> 01:10:50,073
This is no bluff.

1037
01:10:50,154 --> 01:10:52,384
These are my cousins,
Sam and Dave.

1038
01:10:52,474 --> 01:10:54,749
Get these jerks
outta here.

1039
01:11:08,634 --> 01:11:12,388
I'm so proud of you.
I love when you hit people.

1040
01:11:14,114 --> 01:11:16,469
You got a lot
of rules, Jules.

1041
01:11:24,794 --> 01:11:26,944
[ Julius ]
What a day.

1042
01:11:27,034 --> 01:11:30,470
First we visited
our birthplace...

1043
01:11:30,554 --> 01:11:32,510
then we bought
new clothes.

1044
01:11:32,594 --> 01:11:36,143
I got a bucket of ice and
a very good bottle of wine.

1045
01:11:36,234 --> 01:11:39,624
- Then we danced the waltz.
- Yes, we did.

1046
01:11:39,714 --> 01:11:42,706
- It's too bright.
- Then we got into a fight.

1047
01:11:42,794 --> 01:11:46,628
- We have this beautiful room.
- Perfect. Yes, it is beautiful.

1048
01:11:46,714 --> 01:11:48,864
Life just doesn't
get better than this.

1049
01:11:48,954 --> 01:11:52,867
- Oh, yes, it does. Good night.
- Where are you going ?

1050
01:11:52,954 --> 01:11:56,310
I'm gonna go tuck Linda in
and maybe read her a bedtime story.

1051
01:11:56,394 --> 01:11:59,431
Don't wait up for me.
[ Chuckle ]

1052
01:12:07,914 --> 01:12:09,950
[ knocking ]

1053
01:12:10,034 --> 01:12:11,945
Oh, Vincent, you locked
yourself out.

1054
01:12:12,034 --> 01:12:14,025
I--

1055
01:12:14,114 --> 01:12:16,150
- Marnie.
- Hi.

1056
01:12:16,234 --> 01:12:18,065
- Hi.
- Vince and Linda wanna be alone...

1057
01:12:18,154 --> 01:12:21,271
so I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to stay here tonight.

1058
01:12:21,354 --> 01:12:25,552
- You mean you're gonna
sleep here tonight ?
- Uh-huh.

1059
01:12:25,634 --> 01:12:28,467
Which bed should I take ?

1060
01:12:30,754 --> 01:12:33,029
Either bed will be fine.

1061
01:12:33,114 --> 01:12:34,945
I always sleep
on the floo--

1062
01:12:44,074 --> 01:12:47,430
- Good night.
- Good night.

1063
01:12:59,274 --> 01:13:03,153
Julius.

1064
01:13:06,394 --> 01:13:09,864
- Good night.
- Good night.

1065
01:13:25,474 --> 01:13:28,113
- Oh, no.
- What ?

1066
01:13:29,474 --> 01:13:33,023
- What's the matter ?
- This bed is lumpy.

1067
01:13:38,314 --> 01:13:41,386
You mind if I share
the floor with you ?

1068
01:14:07,754 --> 01:14:11,269
You're teasing me,
aren't you ?

1069
01:14:11,354 --> 01:14:13,663
A little.

1070
01:14:16,074 --> 01:14:20,272
What do I do now ?

1071
01:14:23,274 --> 01:14:25,185
We'll figure it out.

1072
01:14:31,034 --> 01:14:33,787
Why are you
doing that now ?

1073
01:14:33,874 --> 01:14:35,705
Mom hasn't seen me
in all these years.

1074
01:14:35,794 --> 01:14:38,024
I wanna look my best.

1075
01:14:41,274 --> 01:14:43,105
And you look
really good.

1076
01:14:43,194 --> 01:14:45,503
I know, I know,
I know, I know.

1077
01:14:45,594 --> 01:14:49,553
So like this.
One, two, three.

1078
01:14:49,634 --> 01:14:51,465
Are you a little nervous ?

1079
01:14:53,474 --> 01:14:55,908
- Just a little.
- Nine, ten.

1080
01:14:55,994 --> 01:14:57,825
- Linda.
- What ?

1081
01:14:57,914 --> 01:15:01,748
Like, what if she's
disappointed in me ?

1082
01:15:01,834 --> 01:15:04,553
If she's disappointed,
then she's a fake.

1083
01:15:04,634 --> 01:15:07,751
I don't know what else
a mom could want in a son.

1084
01:15:07,834 --> 01:15:10,667
- Huh ?
- You're right.

1085
01:15:10,754 --> 01:15:13,552
You're right, you're right.
Why am I worried ?

1086
01:15:13,634 --> 01:15:15,465
- What am I worried about ?
- I don't know.

1087
01:15:15,554 --> 01:15:17,431
You got it all.

1088
01:15:17,514 --> 01:15:22,827
- I couldn't do this without you, Linda.
- Yeah.

1089
01:15:22,914 --> 01:15:25,553
You know,
I've been thinking...

1090
01:15:25,634 --> 01:15:28,990
- that when we get back...
- Yeah ?

1091
01:15:29,074 --> 01:15:31,224
I think we should
move in together.

1092
01:15:31,314 --> 01:15:33,145
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

1093
01:15:33,234 --> 01:15:35,464
- Oh, no, no.
- It's not ''Oh, no.''

1094
01:15:35,554 --> 01:15:37,465
- It's not no, no, no, no, no.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

1095
01:15:37,554 --> 01:15:39,704
I don't want to get married
and it's not that I wanna...

1096
01:15:39,794 --> 01:15:42,149
keep track of you,
because I don't need to.

1097
01:15:42,234 --> 01:15:45,510
I just wanna
live with you.

1098
01:15:45,594 --> 01:15:48,028
It'd be fun.

1099
01:15:48,114 --> 01:15:51,026
Linda, look at me.

1100
01:15:51,114 --> 01:15:53,025
Do I look like somebody
who could play house ?

1101
01:15:53,114 --> 01:15:56,026
I'm cranky in the morning,
I'm grouchy in the afternoon...

1102
01:15:56,114 --> 01:15:58,423
I'm moody at night,
I'm like miserable.

1103
01:15:58,514 --> 01:16:00,744
I know what
you're like.

1104
01:16:00,834 --> 01:16:04,747
Let's sleep on it, okay ?
Sleep on it.

1105
01:16:04,834 --> 01:16:07,143
- Okay, one night.
- This is going to be great.

1106
01:16:07,234 --> 01:16:10,829
Tomorrow I'm taking my best girl
to meet my mom. I'm so excited.

1107
01:16:10,914 --> 01:16:14,384
- Your best girl ?
- Yeah, you, you.

1108
01:16:14,474 --> 01:16:17,784
- Linda, there's no other girls.
Not any more.
- Yeah ?

1109
01:16:17,874 --> 01:16:21,992
- Just you.
- There better not be. know why ?

1110
01:16:31,314 --> 01:16:33,191
- That sounds familiar.
- It's a good song.

1111
01:16:33,274 --> 01:16:35,105
You like that song, huh ?

1112
01:17:17,234 --> 01:17:20,431
Oh, it's huge.

1113
01:17:20,514 --> 01:17:22,345
Oh, it's beautiful.

1114
01:17:22,434 --> 01:17:24,265
Not to mention valuable.

1115
01:17:24,354 --> 01:17:26,663
Real estate like this
is worth a fortune.

1116
01:17:26,754 --> 01:17:28,631
You mustn't always
think about money.

1117
01:17:28,714 --> 01:17:30,830
You got me all wrong,
Julius.

1118
01:17:30,914 --> 01:17:32,347
[ Ringing ]

1119
01:17:32,434 --> 01:17:35,312
I'm just saying
it's nice Mom's loaded.

1120
01:17:35,394 --> 01:17:38,670
That's a worry she won't
have to have in her old age.

1121
01:17:38,754 --> 01:17:40,585
Hello,
can I help you ?

1122
01:17:40,674 --> 01:17:43,268
- Yes, yes, yes.
- Oh, um, excuse me.

1123
01:17:43,354 --> 01:17:45,106
We are looking for
Mary Ann Benedict, please.

1124
01:17:45,194 --> 01:17:47,583
I'm sorry, but
that's not possible.

1125
01:17:47,674 --> 01:17:49,824
Look, we've
come a long way.

1126
01:17:49,914 --> 01:17:53,702
And believe me, she's gonna
be very happy to see us.

1127
01:17:53,794 --> 01:17:57,787
You're gonna have to
write to the Benedict Foundation
stating your business.

1128
01:17:57,874 --> 01:17:59,785
I'm sorry. Good day.

1129
01:18:04,314 --> 01:18:08,387
- Foundation ?
- Millions, Julius.

1130
01:18:08,474 --> 01:18:10,226
Mama's rich.
We gotta go see her.

1131
01:18:10,314 --> 01:18:11,906
Buckaroos.

1132
01:18:11,994 --> 01:18:14,269
- Let's get in there.
We gotta talk to her.
- We sneak in.

1133
01:18:14,354 --> 01:18:16,663
- How is it ?
- Yeah, it's clear. Throw me over.

1134
01:18:16,754 --> 01:18:18,631
Okay.

1135
01:18:21,754 --> 01:18:24,552
Vince ?
Vince, are you okay ?

1136
01:18:24,634 --> 01:18:26,465
Yeah, shut up.
Come on, come on.

1137
01:18:49,274 --> 01:18:51,151
What a lovely day.

1138
01:18:54,914 --> 01:18:59,112
Hey, Vincent, don't you
think this is Mama ?

1139
01:18:59,194 --> 01:19:03,472
It could be. Yeah.

1140
01:19:03,554 --> 01:19:06,626
Don't just stand there.
Go introduce yourselves.

1141
01:19:06,714 --> 01:19:07,863
Hey !

1142
01:19:07,954 --> 01:19:11,310
- Should you people be here ?
- Uh-oh.

1143
01:19:11,394 --> 01:19:15,148
That depends on how you feel
personally about trespassing.

1144
01:19:15,234 --> 01:19:17,702
Does he always try
to be funny like that ?

1145
01:19:17,794 --> 01:19:21,628
- We're looking for
Miss Mary Ann Benedict.
- Yeah.

1146
01:19:21,714 --> 01:19:24,990
- Is she here ?
- Yeah, she's here.

1147
01:19:25,074 --> 01:19:27,463
She's here !

1148
01:19:27,554 --> 01:19:30,193
Sneaking in like that,
I should call the police.

1149
01:19:30,274 --> 01:19:32,424
No, no, no. You don't want
to do anything like that.

1150
01:19:32,514 --> 01:19:36,792
This is not your everyday,
average situation.

1151
01:19:44,394 --> 01:19:46,703
She's our mother,
is the thing.

1152
01:19:46,794 --> 01:19:49,228
- We're her sons.
- Twin sons.

1153
01:19:52,154 --> 01:19:54,304
You're comedians.

1154
01:19:54,394 --> 01:19:56,749
- No.
- No. We--

1155
01:19:56,834 --> 01:19:58,950
We're kind of a surprise.

1156
01:19:59,034 --> 01:20:02,788
I'll bet you are.
Follow me.

1157
01:20:08,354 --> 01:20:11,312
- We were right.
- It is her.

1158
01:20:18,034 --> 01:20:19,990
Excuse me.

1159
01:20:21,674 --> 01:20:23,710
- We thought that this is--
- Mary Ann Benedict ?

1160
01:20:23,794 --> 01:20:26,627
This is an artists' colony.
There are a lot of painters.

1161
01:20:26,714 --> 01:20:30,184
Come on.

1162
01:20:31,634 --> 01:20:33,909
I can't wait to meet her.

1163
01:20:33,994 --> 01:20:35,985
- Yeah.
- It's gotta be amazing.

1164
01:20:36,074 --> 01:20:38,907
Look. Mary Ann Benedict
never understood...

1165
01:20:38,994 --> 01:20:41,554
why people wanted
to buy her paintings.

1166
01:20:41,634 --> 01:20:44,512
But for a brief period,
they were considered valuable.

1167
01:20:44,594 --> 01:20:47,825
She used the money
to buy Whispering Pines.

1168
01:20:49,754 --> 01:20:51,824
May I ask you a question ?

1169
01:20:51,914 --> 01:20:55,748
Why do you keep referring
to her in the past tense ?

1170
01:20:55,834 --> 01:20:58,507
Because...

1171
01:20:58,594 --> 01:21:00,869
she passed away
some time ago.

1172
01:21:02,594 --> 01:21:04,903
She passed--

1173
01:21:04,994 --> 01:21:08,111
You jus-- You just said
she was here.

1174
01:21:08,194 --> 01:21:12,392
I meant, her spirit.
Her spirit is always here.

1175
01:21:15,954 --> 01:21:17,433
Come on.

1176
01:21:41,474 --> 01:21:44,864
Can we get the hell
out of here, please ?

1177
01:21:47,274 --> 01:21:49,913
[ Mary Ann ]
Those damn real estate developers !

1178
01:21:49,994 --> 01:21:53,304
They won't be happy until
they turn this into a golf course.

1179
01:21:53,394 --> 01:21:55,862
Oh, is that
who they were ?

1180
01:21:55,954 --> 01:21:58,627
They're shameless.
They'll try anything.

1181
01:22:00,554 --> 01:22:04,183
Do you know those men claim
to be my twin sons ?

1182
01:22:04,274 --> 01:22:06,390
- If you can believe that !
- What ?

1183
01:22:06,474 --> 01:22:09,034
It was really
quite upsetting.

1184
01:22:09,114 --> 01:22:11,264
Mary Ann, I am sorry.

1185
01:22:11,354 --> 01:22:13,504
It's all right.
It doesn't matter.

1186
01:22:13,594 --> 01:22:15,744
You get over things.

1187
01:22:17,874 --> 01:22:20,308
I did have a child once.

1188
01:22:20,394 --> 01:22:23,113
But he died at birth.

1189
01:22:28,634 --> 01:22:31,307
[ Linda ]
You should be proud of her.

1190
01:22:31,394 --> 01:22:33,510
She donates her house, land...

1191
01:22:33,594 --> 01:22:35,903
and all her paintings
to young artists.

1192
01:22:35,994 --> 01:22:38,872
Linda, do I look like
a young artist ?

1193
01:22:38,954 --> 01:22:41,991
- All she meant--
- I know what she meant,
and why she's here.

1194
01:22:42,074 --> 01:22:44,463
It's got nothing to do
with finding my mother...

1195
01:22:44,554 --> 01:22:46,545
and everything
to do with money.

1196
01:22:46,634 --> 01:22:50,388
- That's not true and you know it.
- Bullshit !

1197
01:22:50,474 --> 01:22:53,386
Take it easy, Vincent.
This is not her fault.

1198
01:22:53,474 --> 01:22:56,193
Look who decided
to chime in !

1199
01:22:56,274 --> 01:22:58,105
The creature from
the Black Lagoon.

1200
01:22:58,194 --> 01:23:00,344
I should've had my head
examined listening to you.

1201
01:23:00,434 --> 01:23:02,345
A deal-of-a-lifetime
opportunity...

1202
01:23:02,434 --> 01:23:05,028
and I'm out looking
for a dead mother.

1203
01:23:05,114 --> 01:23:07,992
- All I wanted was to
make us into a family.
- Family, my butt !

1204
01:23:08,074 --> 01:23:10,190
There's no family here.

1205
01:23:10,274 --> 01:23:13,027
There's nothin' here
except me and three losers.

1206
01:23:13,114 --> 01:23:15,184
I don't know
why I listen to people.

1207
01:23:15,274 --> 01:23:17,504
- I don't know why I do it.
- Cut it out.

1208
01:23:17,594 --> 01:23:19,471
Vince !

1209
01:23:19,554 --> 01:23:21,385
- I'm leaving.
- No, stop !

1210
01:23:21,474 --> 01:23:23,465
Stop ! What are you doing ?

1211
01:23:23,554 --> 01:23:26,148
You're acting
like a fourth-grader.

1212
01:23:26,234 --> 01:23:29,192
Where do you think
you're going ?

1213
01:23:29,274 --> 01:23:32,391
He dumped us in
the middle of New Mexico.

1214
01:23:32,474 --> 01:23:34,669
I can't--

1215
01:23:34,754 --> 01:23:36,585
Julius !

1216
01:23:36,674 --> 01:23:38,983
You don't know this...

1217
01:23:39,074 --> 01:23:41,747
and I promised Vince
that I wouldn't tell you...

1218
01:23:41,834 --> 01:23:45,463
but he's got something in
the trunk that's worth millions.

1219
01:23:45,554 --> 01:23:50,105
I'm worried he's gonna get
himself killed delivering it.

1220
01:23:54,354 --> 01:23:56,868
[ Vince ]
Okay, yeah. Yes, Mr Beetroot.

1221
01:23:56,954 --> 01:24:01,266
Yeah, I'll find it. Yeah.

1222
01:24:01,354 --> 01:24:03,231
Yes, I have a map.

1223
01:24:03,314 --> 01:24:05,350
All right.
I'll see you there.

1224
01:24:05,434 --> 01:24:07,504
See you in Houston
in the morning.

1225
01:24:07,594 --> 01:24:09,983
I'll be looking
forward to it.

1226
01:24:10,074 --> 01:24:12,542
What a coincidence.

1227
01:24:12,634 --> 01:24:14,511
That was our friend.

1228
01:24:14,594 --> 01:24:17,791
Looks like I'm gonna be
doing business with... him.

1229
01:24:17,874 --> 01:24:19,148
Sorry.

1230
01:24:19,234 --> 01:24:21,464
I would have done
the same thing.

1231
01:24:21,554 --> 01:24:24,830
You want the merchandise.
It's not your problem who delivers.

1232
01:24:24,914 --> 01:24:26,666
Precisely.

1233
01:24:32,074 --> 01:24:34,713
But how will
you find him ?

1234
01:24:34,794 --> 01:24:36,625
I have him in my head.

1235
01:24:36,714 --> 01:24:40,309
I found him once,
I'll find him again.

1236
01:24:40,394 --> 01:24:42,624
I hope so. Bye.

1237
01:24:42,714 --> 01:24:44,864
Be careful.

1238
01:26:18,194 --> 01:26:20,025
Sorry I'm late.

1239
01:26:20,114 --> 01:26:24,153
- The directions you gave me weren't--
- Step back.

1240
01:26:26,714 --> 01:26:29,148
Get over here.

1241
01:26:29,234 --> 01:26:31,794
I'm unarmed.

1242
01:26:31,874 --> 01:26:33,865
He's clean.

1243
01:26:33,954 --> 01:26:37,185
Oh, oh.
Isn't that pretty !

1244
01:26:37,274 --> 01:26:39,105
Yeah, it is.

1245
01:26:39,194 --> 01:26:42,311
- Did you come here alone, unarmed ?
- Yeah.

1246
01:26:42,394 --> 01:26:44,350
You're just some fool
who stole a car ?

1247
01:26:44,434 --> 01:26:47,870
Yeah, I guess I am.

1248
01:26:47,954 --> 01:26:50,707
You don't know what
the hell this is, do you ?

1249
01:26:50,794 --> 01:26:53,672
No.

1250
01:26:53,754 --> 01:26:57,190
Revolutionary fuel-injection
system for jets.

1251
01:26:57,274 --> 01:27:00,072
Worth a fortune to the company that
brings it to the market first.

1252
01:27:00,154 --> 01:27:04,227
Somebody else developed it,
but I just had to have it.

1253
01:27:04,314 --> 01:27:06,509
Crafty devil, huh ?

1254
01:27:07,514 --> 01:27:09,664
What are you waiting for ?

1255
01:27:10,914 --> 01:27:12,825
Wait a minute, Beetroot !

1256
01:27:12,914 --> 01:27:15,508
- I thought we had a deal.
- We do.

1257
01:27:24,754 --> 01:27:26,790
Five million bucks !

1258
01:27:26,874 --> 01:27:29,832
- You wanna count it ?
- No, no.

1259
01:27:29,914 --> 01:27:34,430
- But I could use a lift to town.
- Don't press your luck.

1260
01:27:34,514 --> 01:27:36,345
Okay. That's all right.

1261
01:27:36,434 --> 01:27:40,188
I gassed it up for you,
Beetroot. Thank you !

1262
01:27:40,274 --> 01:27:45,029
Five million dollars !
Five million bucks !

1263
01:27:45,114 --> 01:27:48,265
Ha-ha-ha !
Five million bucks !

1264
01:27:48,354 --> 01:27:50,868
- I've gotta look at it !
- [ Crash ]

1265
01:27:52,474 --> 01:27:54,942
Uh-oh.

1266
01:28:33,674 --> 01:28:35,824
Hey, Benedict !

1267
01:28:35,914 --> 01:28:38,667
All I want is the money.

1268
01:28:38,754 --> 01:28:42,508
Just give me what's mine
and I'll leave you alone.

1269
01:29:17,954 --> 01:29:20,184
Steps ! Steps !

1270
01:29:31,114 --> 01:29:33,503
Leave my brother alone.

1271
01:29:34,594 --> 01:29:37,062
No.

1272
01:29:37,154 --> 01:29:38,985
Julius.

1273
01:29:39,074 --> 01:29:42,146
No, no, no.

1274
01:29:42,234 --> 01:29:44,953
No, no.

1275
01:29:47,674 --> 01:29:50,905
Julius, you're--
you're here ?

1276
01:29:50,994 --> 01:29:53,349
No. No, you idiot.

1277
01:29:53,434 --> 01:29:55,550
Don't be nervous.

1278
01:29:55,634 --> 01:29:58,865
I hate violence.
Plus I never carry a gun.

1279
01:29:58,954 --> 01:30:01,422
Who are you ?

1280
01:30:01,514 --> 01:30:03,425
Whoa, whoa, whoa !

1281
01:30:03,514 --> 01:30:05,425
Put the gun down.
I got the money.

1282
01:30:05,514 --> 01:30:08,187
Here's your money.
Here's your money.

1283
01:30:08,274 --> 01:30:11,266
Here's the money.

1284
01:30:11,354 --> 01:30:13,743
You're a goddamned millionaire.

1285
01:30:15,074 --> 01:30:19,545
You, I am never
gonna forgive... never.

1286
01:30:19,634 --> 01:30:23,104
- Open it.
- Open it ?

1287
01:30:23,194 --> 01:30:26,504
You were going
to get killed.

1288
01:30:26,594 --> 01:30:30,143
- I was trying to distract him
so you could escape.
- I already had escaped !

1289
01:30:30,234 --> 01:30:33,590
I was halfway to Brazil
when I felt you !

1290
01:30:33,674 --> 01:30:36,711
- Close it.
- Close it ?

1291
01:30:36,794 --> 01:30:38,830
Open it, close it.
Open it, close it.

1292
01:30:38,914 --> 01:30:42,463
- Why didn't you go ?
- Why didn't I go ?

1293
01:30:42,554 --> 01:30:46,183
Because thanks to you,
I'm not only a goddamned psychic--

1294
01:30:46,274 --> 01:30:47,707
Benedict !

1295
01:30:47,794 --> 01:30:50,262
- I think the case belongs to me.
- Oh, sorry.

1296
01:30:50,354 --> 01:30:54,313
I got this disease
called a conscience.

1297
01:30:54,394 --> 01:30:57,864
- No one ever said being good was easy.
- ''No one ever said--''

1298
01:30:57,954 --> 01:30:59,433
Will you two shut up !

1299
01:30:59,514 --> 01:31:02,153
Butt out, pal !
You got your money.

1300
01:31:02,234 --> 01:31:05,146
Now take it and go live in
the lap of luxury somewhere.

1301
01:31:05,234 --> 01:31:07,350
Try Brazil.

1302
01:31:07,434 --> 01:31:10,665
It doesn't work that way.
You've seen my face.

1303
01:31:10,754 --> 01:31:12,870
Which one's first ?

1304
01:31:12,954 --> 01:31:16,629
You gonna kill us, even though
we gave you the money ?

1305
01:31:16,714 --> 01:31:18,147
You got it.

1306
01:31:18,234 --> 01:31:21,590
Wait, you forgot the third rule
in a crisis situation.

1307
01:31:21,674 --> 01:31:24,905
- The third rule ?
- Third rule ?

1308
01:31:24,994 --> 01:31:27,792
Yeah, third rule.

1309
01:31:31,754 --> 01:31:33,551
Oooh !

1310
01:31:33,634 --> 01:31:36,751
- The third rule.
- What's the third rule ?

1311
01:31:36,834 --> 01:31:38,347
Duck !

1312
01:32:07,114 --> 01:32:09,309
Yo !

1313
01:32:09,394 --> 01:32:12,227
Holy-shmoly !

1314
01:32:17,434 --> 01:32:20,392
Now there's a man
with a lot on his mind.

1315
01:32:23,274 --> 01:32:25,834
Thanks for coming back,
Vincent.

1316
01:32:25,914 --> 01:32:28,712
We're brothers, right ?

1317
01:32:28,794 --> 01:32:30,944
- We're family.
- That's right.

1318
01:32:33,754 --> 01:32:36,109
A rich family.

1319
01:32:36,194 --> 01:32:38,503
- A good family.
- What ? What ?

1320
01:32:38,594 --> 01:32:41,062
- We're gonna return this money.
- No.

1321
01:32:41,154 --> 01:32:43,270
- We don't have to give it back.
- Yes, we do.

1322
01:32:43,354 --> 01:32:45,310
- Why ? Why ?
- We have to, believe me.

1323
01:32:48,594 --> 01:32:51,586
- Mary Ann ?
- Hmm ?

1324
01:32:51,674 --> 01:32:54,711
I think you'd better come
take a look at this.

1325
01:32:54,794 --> 01:32:57,945
What is it ?

1326
01:33:23,354 --> 01:33:24,867
Mary Ann ?

1327
01:33:24,954 --> 01:33:28,867
What a pleasant surprise.

1328
01:33:31,354 --> 01:33:34,232
You stole my family.

1329
01:33:34,314 --> 01:33:37,306
You lying son of a bitch.

1330
01:33:42,874 --> 01:33:45,183
Linda, I'm sorry.

1331
01:33:45,274 --> 01:33:47,742
I made a terrible mistake
and I apologize.

1332
01:33:47,834 --> 01:33:50,428
I-- All I'm asking for
is another chance.

1333
01:33:50,514 --> 01:33:52,391
I know I don't
deserve this--

1334
01:33:52,474 --> 01:33:54,544
That's right,
you don't deserve it.

1335
01:34:09,234 --> 01:34:11,145
Vince ?

1336
01:34:24,834 --> 01:34:28,144
Yes, this is the
Benedict Corporation.

1337
01:34:28,234 --> 01:34:31,271
We are a consulting firm...
a think tank.

1338
01:34:31,354 --> 01:34:34,471
Something like
the Rand Corporation.

1339
01:34:34,554 --> 01:34:36,863
- Only smarter.
- Only smarter.

1340
01:34:36,954 --> 01:34:38,945
Tomorrow at 3:00.

1341
01:34:39,034 --> 01:34:42,310
Yes, I'll put you down.

1342
01:34:42,394 --> 01:34:44,191
Good night, Mr Benedicts.

1343
01:34:44,274 --> 01:34:46,265
- Good night.
- Good night.

1344
01:34:46,354 --> 01:34:49,983
That's it.
The last cheque is written.

1345
01:34:50,074 --> 01:34:53,305
What do we have left out of
the $50,000 reward ?

1346
01:34:53,394 --> 01:34:56,147
After we've paid off
all our debts...

1347
01:34:56,234 --> 01:34:59,032
we have exactly $12,278.

1348
01:34:59,114 --> 01:35:02,743
- $12,278. That's terrible.
- What ?

1349
01:35:02,834 --> 01:35:05,587
You're just upset because
I made you return that suitcase.

1350
01:35:08,354 --> 01:35:11,744
Oh, the money.

1351
01:35:11,834 --> 01:35:14,143
You mean the
four million dollars.

1352
01:35:15,354 --> 01:35:17,663
Four million dollars.
Just say it.

1353
01:35:17,754 --> 01:35:20,871
Say it...
four million dollars.

1354
01:35:20,954 --> 01:35:23,422
It's a lot of money,
Jules.

1355
01:35:23,514 --> 01:35:26,631
Vincent...
I'm very proud of you.

1356
01:35:26,714 --> 01:35:30,343
[ Sighs ]
Well...

1357
01:35:30,434 --> 01:35:33,983
yeah, I'm kinda
proud of myself.

1358
01:35:34,074 --> 01:35:37,305
[ Julius ] lsn't it great to be one
of the good guys for a change ?

1359
01:35:37,394 --> 01:35:40,352
It feels great
to be a good guy !

1360
01:35:40,434 --> 01:35:43,426
You're a great guy, too.
You came back for me, huh ?

1361
01:35:43,514 --> 01:35:46,586
- You did steal a car though.
- I borrowed one.

1362
01:35:46,674 --> 01:35:49,905
I brought it back the next day.
I explained it to the man.

1363
01:35:49,994 --> 01:35:51,712
He was a cowboy.

1364
01:35:51,794 --> 01:35:54,672
Excuse me ? I'm--

1365
01:35:54,754 --> 01:35:58,303
Oh, my God. I don't even know
which one is which.

1366
01:36:02,634 --> 01:36:04,704
I'm sorry.
I didn't know.

1367
01:36:04,794 --> 01:36:07,945
You see, I didn't
believe your story.

1368
01:36:08,034 --> 01:36:10,946
Who would believe
a crazy story like that ?

1369
01:36:14,754 --> 01:36:17,222
They lied to me
all these years.

1370
01:36:17,314 --> 01:36:20,272
They lied to you, too.

1371
01:36:27,034 --> 01:36:30,106
You found each other.

1372
01:36:36,354 --> 01:36:38,470
Now you found me.

1373
01:36:57,234 --> 01:36:59,111
Mama ?

1374
01:37:00,714 --> 01:37:01,942
Mama !

1375
01:37:03,954 --> 01:37:05,387
Mama !

1376
01:37:05,474 --> 01:37:07,704
Oh, Mama !

1377
01:37:25,274 --> 01:37:27,469
Good.

1378
01:37:27,554 --> 01:37:29,704
Tickets ?

1379
01:37:29,794 --> 01:37:31,625
Thanks. This is
gonna be great.

1380
01:37:31,714 --> 01:37:34,433
I just can't get over
how alike they are.

1381
01:37:34,514 --> 01:37:37,506
Yes, it's a beautiful day.

